-- Experian Says CFO Brooks Dies at Home in California
-- B y   P e t e r   W o o d i f i e l d
-- 2012-01-09T09:51:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/experian-says-cfo-brooks-died-suddenly-at-home-in-california.html
(Corrects date Brooks became CFO in second paragraph.)  Experian Plc (EXPN)  Chief Financial Officer
Paul Brooks, 58, died suddenly at his home in  California  at the
weekend, the world’s largest credit-checking company said in a
statement today.  Brooks, who was also a director of Serco Group Plc, had
been chief financial officer of London-based Experian since
October 2001.  “Paul’s legacy to Experian will be the very strong global
finance team he developed, who will provide all the necessary
support and coverage needed as we move forward,” Chairman John
Peace said in the statement  The shares were 2 pence higher at 855 pence at 8.15 a.m. in
London trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Woodifield in Edinburgh at 
 pwoodifield@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at   ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 